quran[12]{c,v,t,f}:
  36,55,"Indeed the companions of Paradise, that Day, will be amused in [joyful] occupation -"
  36,56,"They and their spouses - in shade, reclining on adorned couches."
  36,57,"For them therein is fruit, and for them is whatever they request [or wish]"
  37,40,"But not the chosen servants of Allāh."
  37,41,"Those will have a provision determined -"
  37,42,"Fruits;{1} and they will be honored",footnotes:1:Meaning everything delicious.
  38,19,"And the birds were assembled, all with him repeating [praises]."
  38,20,"And We strengthened his kingdom and gave him wisdom and discernment in speech."
  38,21,"And has there come to you the news of the adversaries, when they climbed over the wall of [his] prayer chamber -"
  39,4,"If Allāh had intended to take a son, He could have chosen from what He creates whatever He willed. Exalted is He; He is Allāh, the One, the Prevailing.{1}",footnotes:1:Refer to footnotes in 12:39.
  39,5,"He created the heavens and earth in truth. He wraps the night over the day and wraps the day over the night and has subjected the sun and the moon, each running [its course] for a specified term. Unquestionably, He is the Exalted in Might, the Perpetual Forgiver.{1}",footnotes:1:Refer to footnotes in 38:66.
  39,6,"He created you from one soul. Then He made from it its mate, and He produced for you from the grazing livestock eight mates.{1} He creates you in the wombs of your mothers, creation after creation, within three darknesses.{2} That is Allāh, your Lord; to Him belongs dominion. There is no deity except Him, so how are you averted?",footnotes:1:See 6:143-144.i.e., the belly, the womb, and the amniotic membrane.